data.text: 11 things people learn too late in life.
One, the less you say, the more your words will matter.
Two, don't take everything personally.
Not everyone thinks about you as much as you do.
Three, when you focus on problems, you'll have more problems.
When you focus on possibilities, you'll have more opportunities.
Four, no matter how much it hurts now,
someday you will look back and realize your struggle changed your life for the better.
Five, you meet people for a reason, either you need them to change your life
or you're the one that will change theirs.
Six, never be afraid to try something new.
Life gets boring when you stay within the limits of what you already know.
Seven, you will never truly know the value of a moment
until it becomes a memory.
Eight, once you begin to take note of the things you are grateful for,
you begin to lose sight of the things that you lack.
Nine, if you do not have control over your mouth,
you do not have control over your future.
Ten, life is a mirror and will reflect back to the thinker what he thinks into it.
You level. The only person you have to face in the morning is yourself.
Be unbeatable.
